cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Layer 2 Latency and Energy Measurement under Variable Traffic Loads
abstract: This dataset captures latency and energy consumption metrics for Layer 2
  packet forwarding under varying packet rates and sizes. The experiment uses synchronized
  traffic generation via MoonGen and controlled forwarding tests on two nodes, with
  configurations ensuring deterministic hardware behavior. Six runs per workload configuration
  measure latency histograms, energy usage, and transmission performance. Archive
  contents include setup scripts, per-run logs, and evaluation outputs for analyzing
  traffic impact on network device efficiency.
